smuxPstatus.name: smuxPstatus
smuxPstatus.description: The type of SMUX peer. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invaliding the corresponding entry in the smuxPeerTable. It is an implementation- specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that correspond to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relative smuxPstatus object.
